The "FLEX UniFLEX" system will consume the most power due to the 3 pieces IDE card 
and 20Mhz FLEX system.

The power consumption is ~15W

Power consumption at 5,000V is ~2,767A
Power consumption at 5,200V is ~2,855A

If both operating systems are active, power consumption will increase slightly.

This measurement was done with the GAL type chips on all PCBs,
Reducing power consumption is possible by using other types
see "PLD and Programmers Info".

Depending on the GALs used, the power consumption can be just above 3Amp,
With a backplane fuse of 3.15A, the fuse wire can slowly sag and
break over time. Then install a 4 or 5 amp type.



Voltage loss across the backplane connections:
   GND Bridges 0V
   +5V Bridge  >1mV

   GND between connector pin 6A - 7C 0mV
   +5V between connector pin 6A - 7C ~2mV

   GND between connector pin 0A - DC ~2mV
   +5V between connector pin 0A - DC ~28mV


A PC power supply is a bit overkill for the system,
a small power supply of 5V/5A and 12V/2A fits in the frame next to the CPU.
And can also power some peripherals.

